FBIS3-34099 "drnes023_r_94001" FBIS-NES-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Feb 1994 India Talks Begin With PRC Group on Border Troop Reduction BK0302111394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 GMT 3 Feb 94 BK0302111394 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The experts group of India and China today began their three-day talks on reduction of troop level along the line of actual control. The 12-member Chinese delegation consisting of top army personnel and diplomats is led by the deputy director in the foreign ministry, Mr. Fu Xuezhang. The Indian delegation is led by the joint secretary in the External Affairs Ministry, Mr. Shiv Kumar Menon.
